AGI - Ukraine accepted the United States proposal for a 30-day immediate ceasefire and to take measures to restore lasting peace. According to a joint declaration by the delegations of the United States and Ukraine gathered in Gedda, Kiev and Washington "have adopted important measures to restore lasting peace for Ukraine".
&nbsp;
The ceasefire "immediate and provisional" may be extended by common agreement between the parties and is subject to the simultaneous acceptance and implementation by Russia.
&nbsp;
American Secretary of State Marco Rubio added that the United States will inform Russia that this is the key condition for achieving peace.&nbsp;
During the talks of Gedda, the Ukrainian delegation made "very clear" that "shares President Donald Trump's vision of peace". He explained to the chroniclers the US National Security Councilman, Mike Waltz, according to which Kiev "made concrete steps and proposals" including accepting the complete ceasefire suggested by the US.&nbsp;
<h2>Zelensky, USA persuade Moscow to accept truce
The United States "must convince" Moscow accepts the ceasefire to which Kiev has already given its way free. This was said by Ukrainian President Volodymyr Zelensky at the conclusion of the talks of Gedda.&nbsp;
Ukraine "is ready for peace". He stated in a note the Ukrainian President Zelensky.
"The American part includes our thesis and accepts our proposals," Zelensky explained. Proposals consisting of three points: "silence in the sky", silence in the sea and "concrete measures to establish confidence", like the delivery of prisoners.
Zelensky expressed satisfaction for the restoration of American military assistance and considers "positive" the US proposal of a ceasefire complete of 30 days throughout the Black Sea and the entire line of the front. "We are ready to take such a step," said the Ukrainian president, "Russia must show its readiness to complete the war or continue it. It is time for full truth."
<h2> Rube: "Now it is up to Moscow to move for the truce"</h2>
"The ball of the truce is now in the field of Russia," said Marco Rubio in the margin of the talks of Gedda that led Kiev to accept a ceasefire of 30 days proposed by the American negotiators.<br> Ukraine and the United States made a "positive pass" during today's talks, said the Secretary of State adding that after the United States "will bring this offer" to the Russians "the ball will be in their field".
Waltz said he will speak with the Russian counterpart "in the coming days" and that Rubio will be with the foreign ministers of the G7 in the next two days.&nbsp;
